    <stitle>13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14613 - REMOVE - SHIFTING CONTROLS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="13">
        <title>SHIFTING CONTROLS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302711">Figure 11</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302711" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302711" filename="../figg13/g1302711.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Shifting Controls</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>AIR CONTROL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the two air lines at the "S" or Supply Port and "P" or End Port of the slave
                    valve on the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302712">Figure 12</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302712" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302712" filename="../figg13/g1302712.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 12. Disconnect Air Lines at Supply Port and End Port</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air line at the splitter cylinder cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302713">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302713" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302713" filename="../figg13/g1302713.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Remove Air Line at Splitter Cylinder Cover</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>If desired, the gear shift lever housing assembly can now be removed from the shifter housing
                        by removing the four bolts from the tower.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two mounting screws in the Roadranger valve cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302714">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302714" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302714" filename="../figg13/g1302714.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Remove Mounting Screws</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the cover down the shift lever to expose the valve ports and disconnect the three
                    air lines (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302715">Figure 15</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302715" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302715" filename="../figg13/g1302715.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 15. Disconnect Air Lines</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the jam nut and turn the valve and nut from the gear shift lever (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302716">Figure 16</hotlnk>). Remove the valve cover, air lines, sheathing and
                    O-rings from the lever.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302716" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302716" filename="../figg13/g1302716.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Turn Valve and Nut From Gear Shift Lever</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Air Filter/Regulator Assembly</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hose between the splitter cylinder and air
                    filter/regulator assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302717" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302717" filename="../figg13/g1302717.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Air Hose Between Splitter Cylinder and Air Filter/Regulator</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect and remove the 1/4 inch I.D. air hoses between the slave valve (inset,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302718">Figure 18</hotlnk>) and the air filter/regulator assembly and range
                    cylinder assembly.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302718" filename="../figg13/g1302718.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Air Hoses Between Slave Valve and Air Filter/Regulator</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two bolts and the air filter/regulator assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302719">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302719" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302719" filename="../figg13/g1302719.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 19. Remove Air Filter/Regulator Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>SLAVE VALVE</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the four retaining bolts and the slave valve from the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302720">Figure 20</hotlnk>)
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302720" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302720" filename="../figg13/g1302720.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 20. Remove Slave Valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the hat-type alignment sleeve from the bore in slave valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302721">Figure 21</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302721" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302721" filename="../figg13/g1302721.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 21. Remove Hat-Type Alignment Sleeve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the spring and plunger pin from the bore in the transmission case (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302722">Figure 22</hotlnk>). Remove the slave valve gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302722" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302722" filename="../figg13/g1302722.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 22. Remove Spring and Plunger Pin</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If necessary, remove the air hose fittings from the slave valve (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302723">Figure 23</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302723" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302723" filename="../figg13/g1302723.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 23. Remove Air Hose Fittings</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>For disassembly and reassembly of piston-type Slave Valve Assembly ONLY, see
                        <hotlnk document="s13027_X1302702.xml" xrefid="x1302702">SLAVE VALVES</hotlnk>. .
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
